{
  "text": "Fritz John's [CITATION_1] classical result says that for every symmetric convex body, B, centered about the origin there is an ellipsoid D such that D \u2282 B \u2282 \u221a nD. This implies that every normed space is (affine) \u221a n-equivalent to R n , so our modified volume bound (9) gives",
